Package: HMINB
Title: Heterogeneous Multiple-Inflated Negative Binomial (HMINB) Model
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Bao", "Yongkang", email = "2024001088@ruc.edu.cn", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implementation of the Heterogeneous Multiple-Inflated Negative Binomial (HMINB) model.
    The model handles multiple inflated counts (e.g., excess zeros, ones, etc.) with 
    individual-specific inflation probabilities modeled by a cumulative logit model.
    Penalized selection is used to automatically choose inflation points.
